FastDev
Welcome to FastDev, a dynamic platform designed specifically for developers! This project aims to foster a collaborative environment where programmers can share knowledge, ask questions, and connect with each other, much like Stack Overflow.

Features
  Create and Share Posts: Users can easily create posts related to programming topics, share insights, and contribute to the developer community.
  Ask Questions: Have a coding problem? Ask the community and get answers from fellow developers who are eager to help!
  Follow and Unfollow: Stay updated with the developers and topics you care about. Follow your favorite users to see their posts and activities in your feed.
  Personalized Feed: View the latest posts from users you follow, and discover new content tailored to your interests.
  Filter for Convenience: Quickly find the information you need using advanced filtering options to sort posts and questions.

Tools
  React: A popular JavaScript library for building user interfaces, allowing for the creation of dynamic and interactive web applications through reusable components.
  Firebase: A platform developed by Google for building web and mobile applications. It provides a variety of tools and services, such as authentication, real-time databases, and cloud storage, to help developers create high-quality apps quickly.
  @reduxjs/toolkit: A set of tools designed to simplify the process of using Redux for state management in JavaScript applications. It provides a more efficient way to write Redux logic and manage application state.
  React-Redux: The official binding library for integrating React with Redux, allowing React components to access the Redux store and dispatch actions easily.
  React Router DOM: A standard library for routing in React applications. It enables navigation among views of various components and allows for the dynamic rendering of components based on the application's URL.
  CSS: A style sheet language used for describing the presentation of a document written in HTML or XML. It allows developers to apply styles, layouts, and visual effects to web pages.
  Tailwind CSS: A utility-first CSS framework that provides a set of pre-defined classes to quickly build custom user interfaces. It promotes a highly modular approach to styling by enabling developers to compose designs directly in their markup.
